deck_excerpt: Swarm the field via dangers discarding fableds. Fiber / Cherubini ll foolish Fabled Kushano / bulb. Fabled ragin, charge warrior and formula net you d
Salamangreats built to stomp the meta.
deck_description:
Great futuristic Salamangreat list specially once we get Dugales or how I call him Douglas. Here is the deck in action https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=98qDf16-knQ and below are card explanations.   Engine: MONSTER Starters and extenders
  • 1x Lady Debug - searches entire deck luckly the deck isn't to normal summon reliant (she is limited).
  • 3x Salamangreat Gazelle - a 1 card Mirage stalio at worst. The best salamangreat monster.
  • 3x Salamangreat Spinny - Do play 3, it has synergy with cynet mining and you always wanna draw it.
  • 3x Salamangreat Foxy - Normal summon of the deck. But you can also use it for the second effect in order to make a R3 by the end of a combo (bamboozle) just make sure not to pop your own fieldspell XD.
  • 1x Salamangreat Jack Jaguar - Typically summoned under Sunlight Wolf, helps with R4 plays. He is what I call a perfect powerful one off.
  • 1x Salamangreat Falco - He is sort of a diff version of Jack jaguar (Sort of why you only play one of each). Another level 4 which revives himself, but he can also retrieve your Salamangreat spells/traps from the graveyard.
  • 1x Salamangreat Fowl - He is a free level 4 (key level) Monster Drop. He increases the deck ceiling with him in a deck you can end on multiple traps + r4 like baguska with high consistency. He is quite searchable and 1 is all you need. He can also send Salamangreat monsters from the hand to the graveyard (Which is sometimes handier then the actual not once per turn effect) to prevent your opponent from activating set cards.
  • 1x Salamangreat Meer - a free monster drop which isn't correct level. With Dugales in a game he gets a slight boost because dugales can draw into him or 3x circle / 3x mining. Still a great OPT extender.
  • 1x Flame buffalo - Just 1 because I prefer summoning foxy/debug. You don't need no more.
  • 1x Salamangreat  Foxer. We are in a backrow heavy format, she combos well with Heatleo and foxy. Better of going second, This deck between Fowl, foxer, foxy and Heatleo has ridicilus backrow hate.
  • 1x Backup Secretary - can be another handtrap if one wishes. She is a free level 3 cyberse drop, and no she doesn't overlap with Mirage stalio restriction as she doesn't activate.
  • 1x Crusadia Reclusia - a free level 3 fire effect monster Drop which can pop anything She can be another handtrap if one wishes because there is lots of anti destruction specifically in this format. Granted I am not satisfied with many handtraps.
  Going second cards - I am running just 9 so in average you should see slightly more then 1 per hand. Some salamangreat engine monsters such as Reclusia, Fowl, Foxie and foxer are already good going second cards. The deck can play through board to an extent so I didnt go for to many going first hate.
  • 2x effect veiler - better then Impermanence so that deck doesn't become to fragile to reboot.
  • 3x ash blossom - Sunlight wolf can add it to the hand. Sometimes you even use it for linking / r3 plays.
  • 2x droll - just a good handtrap.
  • 2x super polymerization - for Salamangreat Violer Chimera and Starving Venom Fusion Dragon.
The best cards in the deck
  • 3x Salamangreat circle - A quickplay searcher which can be retrieved back with Sunlight wolf and falco, it can also protect your links which you need on a field to maximize your trap threat.
  • 3x Cynet mining - Discard salamanagreat > search gazelle > special summon gazelle because you just discarded a salamangreat. This card says special summon gazelle from the deck. Fantastic card.
  • 1x Foolish burial - there are like 5 good targets or so and some people aren't playing this card. It often times sends spinny so that gazelle can send a trap.
  • 1x Salamangreat hearth - holy fk this card is scarry good. It can summon monsters from the hand / grave each turn or mass summon if your Link monsters are "Lets say Geminilink summoned".
  • 1x Fury of fire (Its a salamangreat card) - This card is not out yet in a TCG but in short its like another version of Salamangreat hearth. So just play 2 hearth till we get this card. Oh and the restrictions on this card don't matter because it says "for" the rest of this turn and it usually gives you a free r4 / r3 at the end of a combo or gives you a comeback / follow up  / otk play... quite versitaile card.
  • Salamangreat Sanctuary - People call this card a brick but what it allows is really powerful. In short you can summon the same salamangreat on top of that same salamangreat and then your other salamangreat cards and that monster have bonus effects (I call it Geminilink summon).
  • 1x Salamangreat Rage - Pops bunch of card can be milled then added back with Falco, Sunlight Wolf.
  • 2x Salamangreat Roar - Countertrap which negates anything. Can set itself if you "Geminilink summon" your link.
EXTRA deck
  • Salamangreat Violer Chimera. Super poly destroys a mirror match, I am siding fusion of fire. OTK card
  • Starving venom fusion dragon. Super poly target for Thunderdragon / Orcust boards
  • Number 41. I reccomend siding dweller when he is bad but he is such an annoying card to deal with
  • Number 60: Dugales of Forgotten time - A REASON WHY THIS BUILD IS FUTURISTIC  Dugales can extend your plays with first effect which triggers falco btw, or he can revive Tapir for lulz. And it can also help you OTK with his last doubling attack effect. Until he gets out I reccomend update jammer combo for OTK
  • Salamangreat mirage stalio - An invoker for Salamangreat which also acts as monster removal. Only 1 because Jack jaguar keeps puting him back in the deck
  • Bamboozle - he bamboozles monster effects and makes both players draw a card. R3 Distruption
  • Borreload - to out problematic stuff
  • 2x Salamangreat Heatleo - Outs backrow, manipulates the attack of one monster on the field if Geminilinksummoned (Ofc you need more then 1 to geminilinksummon)
  • 3x Sunlight Wolf - This is the most important Salamangreat card. He ensures you have a follow up play for the next turn usually by adding back gazelle unless falco bounces her, also he sets up your backrow
  • 2x Veilynx - you do need 2 for the combos sometimes. There is no space for the third. she can protect your salamangreat monsters from destruction
  • Hiita the blazing fire charmer - she is a shortcut for Heatle if your opponent has a fire monster in the gravyeard, upon being destroyed she searches fire monsters
Side deck Side deck should be, 1 fusion of fire to otk going second, mystic mine hate, handtraps for combo decks, dweller instead of 41, Knightmare phoenix if you are up against heavy and I mean heavy backrow deck   Salamangreats have fantastic battle manipulator Raccoon. this card can fk up any deck which wants to gain advantage in battlephase or Otk you. So this can be sided against Trains, Lunalight, and Crusadia to stop the Otks or against Idk deskbot 004 Esque monsters. I rec siding one because if you ever notice a match-up he ll work in you ll be able to access him since he is searchable. Salamangreats also have fantastic comeback card. Salamangreat Mole. He can help you comeback after evenly / double exciton effect. so in a matchups where the opponent blows up your board why not have this card in a sidedeck to combat this

deck_excerpt:
ISOLDE DATABASE, Collection of great cards on one place which are relevant for / because of Isolde.
Generically good cards which help summoning Isold
deck_description:
Every Card which is good at facilitating the summon of Isolde or gets summoned / searched by it. This is not a deck profile, this is just a collection of Good Warrior cards for our beloved Isolde. My name Is Poske Yugituber. Consider checking me out. I am trying to reach 10 000 SUBS ON youtube.  Below you ll find explanation for every card in Isolde database. This list can help you invest in cards. I recc reading it because there wasn't enough space in a deck for all the relevant warriors. One card Isolde cards
  • Reinforcement of the army - Because it searches One card isolde warriors
  • Armageddon knight - I am sure everyone knows which malicious boy this guy sends
  • Dark Grepher - See above
  • Vision hero Vyon - See above
  • Summoner monk > Discard a spell summon any of the above > abuse the malicious boy
  • Curios the Lightsworn Dominion (LINK) - see above slightly further, no I am not teasing you.
  • Neo space Connector - Summon aqua dolphin > bait a handtrap > Isolde (BEST ONE)
  • Hero lives - Stratos > search any hero > normal summon it pop off with it later enjoy the isolde
  • Golden Castle of Stromberg / Terraforming > summon  Hans > he summons Knight > enjoy the Isolde,
  • Goyo Defender > if you can summon a level 3 synchro you can summon isolde
  • MX saber Invoker > summon lvl 4 earth warrior like kizaru enjoy the invoker (RIP INVOKER THO)
  • Stratos / E call + any Hero if you search Varis or empty hand with Bubbleman > enjoy the Isolde
  • Marauding Captain > Summon any warrior from the hand > Isolde
  • Goblindbergh > summon any warrior from the hand careful they might miss timing
  • Mauled Captain > revive a warrior > Isolde
  • Marmiting Captain > Channel YugiMoto out of yourself reveal a warrior > Isolde
  • Trident warrior > He is sort of a worse marauding captain because he only summons lvl 3 warriors but he has higher stats. (I would never invest in this card)
  • Doppel warrior > synchro with him and you ll get 2 warrior tokens > Isolde
  • Hero kid > special summon him and you ll be able to summon even 2 Isoldes
  • Tuning / Junk Synchron > revive a lvl 2 or lower lvl warrior > Isolde
  • Angrappler > when he does battle dmg revive a warrior > Isolde
  • Chaos End Master > when she destroys something in battle and sends it to the graveyard > Isolde
  • Road warrior > summon a lvl 2 warrior like hero kid > Isolde > Isolde > Isolde
  • Rusty Bardiche > Send cloak by setting a brigadine > search boots > activate brigadine > boots
  Archetype specific 1 card Isoldes 
  •  Kageki / Smoke signal + six sam in hand.
  •  Gouki Supplex + Gouki in Hand
  •  Gouki Rematch with 2 Goukis in Graveyard
  •  Destiny hero Drilldark with destiny hero in hand
  •  Elemental hero Solidguy with E hero in hand
  •  Sattelarknight Altair + Sattelarknight in grave
  •  Sattelarknight Vega + Sattelarknight in hand
  •  Noble Knight Ivyane + noble knight equiped to it > warrior token > Isolde
  •  Noble Knight brothers + Noble knights in hand
The best Warrior Drops (Half off Isolde)
  • Junk forward - if you control no monsters
  • Shade brigadine - if you dont have traps in grave, Boots, cloak and gloves can all get you this
  • Kagemucha knight - when you normal summon a level 3 monster
  • Spell striker - by banishing a spell card (I recc him for six samurai)
  • Hornet bit - free warrior token (Keep in mind having warriors in grave is important for phoenix blade)
  • Sky striker engage searching the hornet bit
  • Spyral super agent - You just Pegasus predict whats on top of their deck
  • Doppel warrior - if you revive any monster
  • Palladion of the sacred tree - If there is a link pointing to your side
  • Blue Mountain Butterspy - If you normal summon a warrior
  • Photon trasher - if you control no monsters. that 2100 attack
  • Super quantum red layer - if you control no monsters
  • U.A Signing deal - summons a warrior U.A from the deck underated engine
  • Instant fusion - Invoked Raidjin is the best target
  • Boost warrior - if you control a tuner
  • The PK silent boots - if you control a bardiche (happens often so mentioned)
  • Overlay booster - if you control a 2000 atk monster
  • T.G Striker / DODODO Buster / Heroic challenger Assault Halberd / Lord gaia the fierce knight / GillaGillancer / Elder of the six samurai / GillaGillalancer (Tbh he is good in six sam as long as invoker is legal), they can all be summoned if you dont and your opponent does control a monster. DIFF levels (Most are Outclased)
  • Doggy Diver - if your opponent controls a monster and you control only and atleast 1 level 4
  • Puppet King - when your opponent searches a monster you can special summon him (Interesting)
  • Card breaker - summons himself by sending 1 face up spell / trap card from your zone (interesting)
  • Performapal life swordsman - when your opponent gains lifepoints SS him (Yeah ll never be relevant)
  • Gagaga Gardna  - when you get direct. attacked SS from hand discard a card immune to battle destruc
  • Tasuke Knight - while you have no cards in your hand and he is in the graveyard and your opponent declares a direct attack. You can SS him and end the battlephase
  • Bubbleman / E call - if your hand is empty
  • Lightray grepher - banish a level 5 or higher. He is alike Dark grepher but for banish zone massive potentional good investment.
  • Empowerment - A fieldspell which summons Pendulum warriors from deck by discarding a card
  • Big one warrior - send a level 1 monster to the graveyard to SS him
The best summons off Isolde
  • Dawn Knight - might get OP in future sends a light monster to the graveyard when he is sent there
  • Brushfire knight - might get OP in future. When fire monster is destroyed send fire monster from the deck to the graveyard. when he is destroyed do the same
  • Hero kid - I recc going into Mannequin cat after
  • Arma / Vyon / Grepher - all can send mali. 2 of them can send dark monsters. Vyon can search poly
  • Elemental hero Prisma - its just interesting this card can be accessed from deck
  • Attack gainer (Just a level 1 earth warrior tuner > ez natbeast)
  • Doppel warrior - I mean doppel has massive potentional to even get banned trust me.
  • Junk Collector - Banishes itself and one normal trap from the graveyard to use its effect (Condition and requirements must be correct but holy thats cool)
  • Dragonox - he can revive but to face down position
  • Altitude Knight - when monster is bounced send a wind monster from deck (some potentional)
  • Shore knight - when his battle position is changed send a water monster from deck (some potentional) maybe with Karkakuris
  • A/D changer - level 1 which changes battle position. I saw this card see some play.
  • Dark Scorpion Chick the Yellow - anyone wants some loops=???
  • Great shogun shien - if you are a madman who plays 7 equips. Maybe in a year 2o25 when we finally get good equips.
Overall Knight cards are worth investing in. Aside from Dust knight I didn't mention which has Flip based earth mill. The best equips for warriors (Quite certain nothing else ll see play)
  • Phoenix blade > Free discard, Dystopia triggerer, Banishes BLS ritual support monsters triggering their search effects, free revive for zepyhros
  • D.D.R > not once per turn, Zephyros and powertool synergy often revives not once per turn Arma
  • Moon mirror shield > card which can return to the deck. Decent overall
  • Sword of Deap Seated > card which stays in deck no matter the discards / mills / being sent to grave
  • Overdone Burial > Equips are kinda bad, semi decent revival
  • Living fossil > see above (Lots of Warrior equips feel like just worse monster reborn)
  • Autonomous action unit > revives opponents monsters, got better with time due to handtraps
  • Cursed bamboo sword / bamboo sword > can be used with golden bamboo sword for draw power
  • Axe of fools > negate a monster effect (A budget forbidden chalice)
  • Noble arms Arfeudutyr > Some backrow hate
  • Snatch steal > its banned but it can honestly come back
  • Second coming of the monarchs >  Isolde monarchs are a thing, it revives monarch stat monster
  • Galaxy zero > Galaxy photon decks can spam Isolde and they already have decent equip. revives galaxy / photon monster
  Photon Warrior spam engine Photon trasher, galaxy braver, photon vanisher, photon advancer, accelight, photon lizard, Overlay booster, Guardian of order (Altho guardian ain't needed dropped it with braver in game) By playing bunch of this you ll have a bunch 2 card Isolde combos. I suggest summoning Hero Kid off Isolde   The best cards to search off Isolde
  • Dragonox - Underated LL combo well with Appolousa. stops battlephase
  • Necro gardna - stops 1 attack but he is quite resiliant card and worth discarding unlike dragonox
  • Black luster soldier - Do I have to explain the BLS
  • Super agent - Some backrow removal + by that time you ll know what you are up against so higher Pegasus predictions.
  • Silent swordsman - a searchable spell negator is nice
  • Lightray gearfried - So much restrictions but maybe he ll find his place someday
  • Destiny hero Plasma - if you are a madman who thinks he ll have enough to facilitate him next turn

deck_name: MIKO TURBO OCG FTK (18 DIFF cards are 1/1.5 card FTK)
deck_excerpt: IB TURBO DECK. There are 18 one card Ftk combos in this deck. All hail the IB and Gandora-x. I don't see whats stoping this deck from taking some tour
deck_description:
Here is a video because motion is more then words but below I ll explain each card https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t3P1yGAaQek   Cruical thing. As long as you can make IB and put a dragon vannila in the graveyard you have an FTK   1 CARD FTKS (18)
  • Treasure Pander - as long as you can put a 1 spell in the graveyard he is an FTK. Note he can even do more as he is not OPT. There are enough spells to facilitate him most of them even draw
  • Cynet mining / Draconet - summon a lvl 2 vannila > you can summon the IB > proceed to FTK
  • Lonefire / Scorpio > search instant fusion > cerubini > send > carboneddon > carboneddon summons a normal tuner him + monster off instant fusion = IB > proceed with guardragon stuff for FTK
  • Fossil Dig / Oviraptor > send carboneddon > summon lvl 1 dragon vanila  > IB
  • Summoner Monk + spell > oviraptor / plant route / treasure pander route
  • Mathematician > carboneddon > summon lvl 2 normal dragon
Note fossil dig can be an extender to make your combo less fragile to handtraps since it searches carboneddon and since Cynet / plant stuff discard him Since this deck is full of 1 card FTKS you can run so many anti handtraps its funny XD
  • 3 Called by the grave
  • 3 Crossout Designator (free activation for panda, you need to main lots of Popular handtraps for this)
  • 3 Dragged down into the grave (An upstart to draw into your ftk cards + removes handtraps LUL), it basically never matters what they discard
  Extenders (Fossil dig and carboneddon already mentioned)
  • Unexpected dai. Well it puts a vannila on the field ...
  • Shaddoll fusion sending carboneddon to the graveyard
  • Foolish burial > it puts a vannila on the field by putting carboneddon in grave or draws with shadd beast
  • Instant fusion + lvl 1 vannila or unexpected dai is an ftk
Draw cards
  • In case you don't draw one of your 18 1 card FTKS
  • 3x Magical mallet - NO THIS IS NOT A BAD CARD 
  • Already mentioned 3X dragged down
  • Shaddoll fusion sending the only target shaddoll beast for draw 1
So yeah its really not a 60 card deck with this much draw power, the deck only has few bricks but you would still rather go to 60.   Handtraps in general (since this deck is full of 1 card engines it can play many) and for Crossout. Crossout has to send from the deck
  • 2x Maxx C (this is the most popular handtrap in the ocg)
  • 2x Ash (the card is limited but stillalso stops maxx C so why not)
  • 1x Droll
  • 1x veiler (also stops maxx C)
  • 2x Impermanence (Crossout negates traps to, Imp aint once per turn)
  • 1x Belle
  • 1x Ghost ogre
There is also 1 pankratops as second oviraptor search target and being decent in general (If any other handtrap you think is popular like d.d crow except for Phantazmei as he doesn't stop you add it) Combo pieces
  • Lvl 1 Vannila dragon tuner (Flamvell guard)
  • Lvl 2 vannila dragon tuner (Lustia the guardragon)
You need both as different 1 card ftks require diff ones
  • 2X Carboneddon (Because you don't mind drawing it + you like having him in deck at all times)
  • 1x Fairy dragon Larvalaur searches the gandora
  • 1x gandora x (It with Equimax at 8k is an FTK > Equimax points to Saryuja and Archfiend Abyss)
  • Predaplant darling cobra
  • World chalice guardragon > IB summons from deck / grave so if you draw him discard him.
  Extra deck is all just combo pieces. Everything is needed sort off. Lambda is there because you gotta link of shekk. Raidjin is just good in case you had the extenders. in case fiber gets handtraped why not draw with formula. Side deck should be more handtraps and mystic mine hate.

This is my version of the Destiny HERO deck to go along side today's meta. So far it is a decent deck that can be used competitively. If you have any opinions on this deck I encourage you to share it. Any alterations can be made to help strengthen it.

deck_excerpt: Ancient Gear Golem,Ancient Gear Golem - Ultimate Pound,Ancient Gear Frame,Ancient Gear Wyvern,Ancient Gear Hunting Hound,Ancient Gear Fusion,Overload
deck_description:
the point of this deck is to go out to Chaos Ancient Gear Giant. your going to be use Trade-In and Hand Destruction most of the time and
Ancient Gear Fortress to protect Ancient Gear Wyvern, Frame and Hunting Hound. you're going to use frame, link slayer, Trade-In and Hand Destruction to send monsters to the grave to mill the deck for Overload Fusion or get to Ancient Gear Fusion. i run Called by the Grave and Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring just for defense against gnomaterial and Ash Blossom or effect veiler. Ancient Gear Castle is more for the counters on this card so you can Tribute this card. i use Scapegoats During my opponent's turn then if i can go out to Borreload Dragon.  in the extra deck category you have Ancient Gear Howitzer, Ultimate Ancient Gear Golem and Ancient Gear Megaton Golem let's say you got Overload Fusion and not enough materials in grave go out to Ancient Gear Howitzer it needs 2 "Ancient Gear" monsters  and Unaffected by other cards' effects. During your Main Phase: You can inflict 1000 damage to your opponent. You can only use this effect of "Ancient Gear Howitzer" once per turn. Your opponent is going to need to get rid of it and when its destroyed by battle and sent to the Graveyard: You can Special Summon 1 "Ancient Gear" monster from your Deck, ignoring its Summoning conditions.  Next is Ultimate Ancient Gear Golem "Ancient Gear Golem" + 2 "Ancient Gear" monsters it's not great but If this card is destroyed, you can Special Summon 1 "Ancient Gear Golem" from your Graveyard, ignoring the Summoning conditions. Next is Ancient Gear Megaton Golem its generic it needs 3 "Ancient Gear" monsters f this card was Fusion Summoned using 2 or more "Ancient Gear Golem" and/or "Ancient Gear Golem - Ultimate Pound" as material, it can attack up to that many times during each Battle Phase. If this face-up Fusion Summoned card in its owner's control leaves the field because of an opponent's card effect: You can Special Summon 1 "Ultimate Ancient Gear Golem" from your Extra Deck, ignoring its Summoning conditions. It good but Called by the Grave is spooky. Chaos Ancient Gear Giant is the ace of the deck it needs 4 "Ancient Gear" monstersMust be Fusion Summoned and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. Unaffected by Spell/Trap effects. Your opponent's monsters cannot activate their effects during the Battle Phase. This card can attack all monsters your opponent controls, once each. If this card attacks a Defense Position monster, inflict piercing battle damage to your opponent. It's got 4500 attack if they have two or more there died you go into game to rinse and repeat  side deck we got Ancient Gear Engineer it Negate any Trap effects that target this card, and if you do, destroy that Trap Card. If this card attacks, your opponent cannot activate any Spell/Trap Cards until the end of the Damage Step. At the end of the Damage Step, if this card attacked: Target 1 Spell/Trap Card your opponent controls; destroy that target. Next we got Keeper of Dragon Magic If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can discard 1 card; add 1 “Polymerization” Normal Spell or “Fusion” Normal Spell from your Deck to your hand. Or it can reveal 1 Fusion Monster in your Extra Deck; Special Summon 1 of the Fusion Materials whose name is specifically listed on that card from your Gy in face-down Defense Position. You can only use each effect of “Keeper of Dragon Magic” once per turn. You cannot Special Summon monsters from the Extra Deck, except Fusion Monsters, the turn you activate either of this card's effects. Double Summon it's self explanatory, Foolish Burial Send 1 monster from your Deck to the Graveyard. It's more for overload fusion. Geartown is the feld spell Both players can Normal Summon "Ancient Gear" monsters for 1 less Tribute. When this card is destroyed and sent to the Graveyard: You can Special Summon 1 "Ancient Gear" monster from your hand, Deck, or Graveyard. Ancient Gear Fortress During the turn they were Normal or Special Summoned, your opponent cannot target "Ancient Gear" monsters you control with card effects, and they cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects. Your opponent cannot activate cards or effects in response to the activation of "Ancient Gear" cards and effects. If this card is destroyed in the Spell & Trap Zone: You can Special Summon 1 "Ancient Gear" monster from your hand or Graveyard, also you cannot Special Summon monsters for the rest of this turn, except "Ancient Gear" monsters. Twin Twisters Discard 1 card, then target up to 2 Spell/Trap Cards on the field; destroy them. Ancient Gear Reborn Once per turn, if you control no monsters: You can target 1 "Ancient Gear" monster in your Graveyard; Special Summon it, and if you do, it gains 200 ATK (even if this card leaves the field). You can only control 1 "Ancient Gear Reborn".

deck_excerpt: Combination of buster blader destruction sword cards and archfiend dragon synchros.  Non-link deck.
deck_description:
Pretty straightforward.  A perfect hand would mean that you drew at least one buster whelp and one buster blader.  Normal summon the whelp, get a dragon buster destruction sword to your hand, special summon your buster blader using whelp's first effect, attach the destruction sword, special summon the destruction sword, synchro summon into a buster dragon, and finally use buster dragon's effect to resummon buster blader from the GY.  At the start of your opponents turn, use buster dragon's other effect to reattach the destruction sword card to your buster blader, barring your opponent from summoning from the extra deck.

Once you have this field, you just build off of it.  Maybe fusion summon your dragon destroyer swordsman, or  use red resonator to give you some extra life points while summoning a powerful dragon archfiend, or use yours and/or your opponents monster to super poly into a five headed dragon.  But that's just extra spice. The deck is built around getting that ideal field in which I explained in the first paragraph as quickly as possible--the rest comes later.

deck_excerpt: True Draco Sky Striker Control (Post January 2019 Banlist)
deck_description: So I've been testing the theory of combining True Dracos and Sky Strikers on ygopro. I think the ability to pop a spell card using Dragonic Diagram and then being able to use Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage! to heavily search and draw is a brilliant idea. The deck did pretty well in testing. Your beginning turn should look like, using your Sky Striker cards and attempting to gain massive card advantage in hand, bringing out Sky Striker Ace - Shizuku, and then tribute summoning your True Draco continuous spell and trap cards using your True Draco cards, like True Draco Heritage to summon a True Draco monster, or a couple if you have the other True Draco continuous spell card, True Draco Disciples. You want to go first, although it can go second without any problems, as long as you're not facing any variant of Thunder Dragons. Thunder Dragon Colossus definitely shuts down this deck very fast, which is why a big chunk of the side deck is dedicated to the Thunder Dragon match up. Another couple of hard match ups are Orcust and Cyber Dragons, which is why I came up with the idea to side System Down, also ABC is still a thing as well. System Down really eliminates Orcust if it resolves since their entire engine is Machine type. You have to bait their Orcust counter trap first and then use it and there's nothing they can do to stop it. So using something like Engage first which they will want to negate, and then once they do, use System Down and they will immediately realize the game is over haha. Once again, I think Book of Moon is a seriously underrated card, it has won me many games because of being able to force your opponent to negate it if your going second and they have negates on board is great. You can activate Book of Moon to target their card that can negate, for example Odd-Eyes Vortex Dragon and they will have to negate it with that monster or a different monster otherwise they won't be able to use its negate effect since it becomes face-down and unknown. Not only that, but going first if you shut down their normal summon to make their monster unknown, it can really hurt them depending on the match up. Like against Salamangreat being able to Book of Moon their normal summon really hurts them because then they can't link off or activate Salamangreat Spinny in grave since they don't control a Salamangreat monster and will most likely have to pass their turn. Also, I know being able to OTK with True Draco and Sky Striker in general is a problem, which is why I added Hiita The Fire Charmer, Ablaze because she can special summon an opponent's fire monster from their graveyard, and then you can go into Knightmare Unicorn or Ningirsu The World Chalice Warrior and clear their board for an OTK. You can also summon another monster and go into Borrelsword Dragon, which 90% of the time finishes the game, or they scoop before hand haha. Anyways, I hope you guys have a fun time playing the deck, and of course, stick around for more!

Shay Obsidian, known as Shun Kurosaki[6][7][8] (黒くろ咲さき 隼しゅん Kurosaki Shun) in the Japanese version, is one of the characters in the Yu-Gi-Oh! ARC-V anime. He is a Duelist from the Xyz Dimension who is one of Yuto's comrades and serially attacked the Leo Institute of Dueling with the intention of rescuing his younger sister Lulu Obsidian. But over time, Yuya and Zuzu convinced Sora to change his ways, and he ultimately switched sides to join them in their battle against Duel Academy.

• The main feature of this deck is sending certain monsters to the Graveyard intentionally to activate their effects (Quickdraw Synchro + Night Assailant + Sangan; ... ), special summoning them (Junk Synchron, Synchron Explorer),  and recovering them from the GY (Rush Warrior, Night Assailant).
  • In most of the times, you'll be able to Summon a LV 5, 7 or 8 Synchro monster in a turn or 2. With a Quickdraw Synchron, Junk Synchron, Phantom Skyblaster, (...)
  • Between summoning a LV 5, 6 or 7 using a Junk Synchron (or even a Quickdraw Synchron), the advisable is summon a Junk Gardna; it's effect of changing a monster's battle position is useful AF.
  • Let's say that in your first turn, you got a Quickdraw Synchron, a Junk Synchron, a Doppelwarrior, a Jet Synchron and 1 another card in your hand: You can special summon Quickdraw Synchron by discarding Jet Synchron, then normal summon Junk Synchron to special summon Jet Synchron from the GY, then use Doppelwarrior's effect and special summon it from your hand. So, synchro summon Nitro Warrior by using Quickdraw Synchron + Doppelwarrior. If summoned succesfully, use Doppelwarrior's effect to summon 2 LV 1 Doppel Tokens. Now, synchro summon Stardust Dragon with Nitro Warrior + Jet Synchron. After that, special summon Jet Synchron using it's effect, sending to the GY the last card in your hand. Use Jet Synchron + a Token to summon Formula Synchron, then Stardust Dragon + Formula Synchron to bring Shooting Star Dragon on the battlefield, on your first turn. Of course, using your' entire hand.

deck_excerpt: Dark Magician Deck with Bond Between Teacher And Student for added spice.
deck_description:
With the release of new support for the dark magician. Bond between teacher and student is one of the best cards available for dark magician. The main strategies of the deck are the basic control and interruption plays that dark magician are known for, but with added spice. With your Dark Magic Circle, Eternal Soul and Magicians Navigation allowing you negations and banishment to your opponent the deck is a underrated rouge strategy. Ash Blossom and Infinite Impermanence are needed in the deck for added protection because the deck is vulnerable to hand traps itself.

Bond Between Teacher And Student is effectively a reverse sages stone, allowing you to summon Dark Magician Girl from anywhere, then allowing you a deck search to set your powerful advantage cards. Dark Burning Magic is without a doubt the best card to search for, Dark Magic Twin Burst is not as good but I feel is a good one of tech card that you can if you wanted to switch out for other cards, but it does have its uses. The Spellbook draw engine is used perfectly with this deck, instantly making your Dark Magic inheritance live as well as being brilliant draw power for any spellcaster deck.

In my side deck are multiple cards i feel have their uses, Mahad is perfect if you are going against a DARK attribute deck. other cards like secret village and epidemic virus can shut down your opponent before they get a chance to combat against your board.

1. Kaiju a monster of the opponent and then steal it with Natasha
2. Nuke the entire board with Black Rose, but protect your monster by banishing the ritual card
3. Building up your graveyard via Michaels mill for Natasha, and then link climb with her by special summoning her from the grave and snatching monsters from the enemy.

Those are just a few strategies that you can do with the deck. And it's finally a good ritual deck without abusing the impcantation cards

Rex Goodwin, sometimes romanized as Rex Godwin, was a major character in Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's. Goodwin was a former developer from R.R.D., head of Sector Security, the man from the Daedalus Bridge legend and the primary antagonist at the end of the Dark Signers arc. He is the only Dark Signer to not wear a cloak and the only Dark Signer to not have his dark mark on his right arm (instead, he had it on his back). He bears the dark mark of the Condor and his Earthbound Immortal is Wiraqocha Rasca. His brother, Roman, entrusted Rex with the mission to use the Signers to someday stop him, as Roman became a Dark Signer. Rex used his influence to gather the Signers and assist them, but secretly used them in order to become a Dark Signer and absorb the powers of a Signer by using Roman's birthmark, and hoped to recreate the world as a god (however, in Z-one's time-line he was not a Dark Signer[2]).

This deck is built on Coin Flip/ Dice Roll chances, so to be clear all the pre-planning and strategy may go wron in an instance- but still it's fun using this deck. Now let's highlight ideas that been followed through during this deck building-
  1. Stall for as long as you can until you get the right card/cards. to help you stalling I added Spell-mining Cave. Using this card is quit effective against the deck that mostly relies on monster effect- like Knightmare Phonix etc. As well as prevents your opponents from attacking you as long as you have less monster than them. mean while you can prepare to assemble desired cards to spring out syncro/ xyz monsters. But never use Spell-mining Cave on your 1st turn while going first, you'll just lose this card. Though Umi deck users or who have cards like harpies fether duster may easily get rid on this card.
  2. your Second protection is Dark sanctuary, though it may not full proof protection like Spell-Mining Cave but atlist gives you a chance to inflict damage on opponent if you flip head. It is advised to use Second Coin Toss with it to have better chance flipping Head.
  3.  Use Spell Reproduction to get back Cup of Ace from GY. so you can keep drawing cards.
